To such we may reply that what these animatis-eat is the con· secrated Host, which is but the sacrament, not Christ’s body or His blood. When a lion devours a man, it does not also deaour his soul;, yet his soul is present in every part of his' body. lt is thus also with the Sacrament ol the Altar;³ it is quite as really present, in a sacra· mental, spiritual or virtual manner (sacramentaliter, spiritualiter vel virtualiter), in every part ol the consecrated Host, as the soul is present in the body.
